				\begin{document}$${Z}^{\prime}factor=1-\frac{3\left({\sigma }_{p}+{\sigma }_{n}\right)}{\left|{\mu }_{n}-{\mu }_{p}\right|}$$\end{document}Z′factor=1-3σp+σnμn-μpwhere σp is the SD of the positive control, σn is the SD of the negative control, μp is the average of the positive control, and μn is the average of the negative control.

